WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

00:13.464 --> 00:14.730
Good morning, Alex.

00:14.764 --> 00:16.329
What's so good about it?

00:16.364 --> 00:19.100
This morning, my mom made
me butterfly-shaped waffles.

00:19.134 --> 00:22.967
I mean, it's the crack of dawn,
stop being adorable.

00:23.001 --> 00:26.168
I made those. Your mom is right.

00:26.203 --> 00:28.002
We should just give you dry toast.

00:29.837 --> 00:32.604
Is Max talking to a girl?

00:32.639 --> 00:36.639
I say three seconds before she
yells "gross" and runs away.

00:39.842 --> 00:42.542
She's not running away.

00:44.044 --> 00:46.778
Let's see if we can't figure
out what's wrong with her.

00:46.812 --> 00:48.578
I know it's here someplace.

00:48.613 --> 00:51.079
This morning, I took it
from my bag of dead things.

00:52.748 --> 00:54.214
Give me a second.

00:54.249 --> 00:57.282
Here it is! All right, my lizard.

00:57.316 --> 01:01.350
Well, most of him. His tail
turned to crumbs in my pocket.

01:02.552 --> 01:04.218
Oh, wait, is this cookie crumbs?

01:08.522 --> 01:09.822
No, that's lizard.

01:12.458 --> 01:15.225
- Here you go.
- Aww.

01:15.259 --> 01:18.494
You know what they say,
"If you love something let it go,

01:18.528 --> 01:20.862
if it doesn't come back it was
never yours in the first place."

01:22.098 --> 01:25.032
But, Tom, it's dead.

01:27.934 --> 01:29.868
Max? Hey!

01:33.071 --> 01:36.140
Did you just give this girl
your most prized possession?

01:36.174 --> 01:38.341
You let her have your dead lizard?

01:38.376 --> 01:39.475
But you got all worked up

01:39.510 --> 01:42.711
when I wanted to turn it into a barrette.

01:42.745 --> 01:46.880
- Tom, who are these people?
- I have no idea, Nancy.

01:46.914 --> 01:51.215
And for your information, total strangers,

01:51.249 --> 01:52.816
we're going to some place in the school

01:52.850 --> 01:54.884
where we actually know people.

01:54.918 --> 01:57.720
Tom, you're so funny.

01:57.754 --> 02:01.022
I know, right? Isn't Tom a riot?

02:01.056 --> 02:03.456
Look, Nancy, it's been a
pleasure meeting both of you,

02:03.490 --> 02:06.058
but, um, I need to talk to
my new friend Tom alone.

02:06.093 --> 02:08.526
OK. I'm going to wood
shop to make a shadow box

02:08.561 --> 02:10.595
- to display my dead lizard.
- OK.

02:12.864 --> 02:15.932
Aw, that's how it all started with me.

02:15.966 --> 02:18.233
Shadow boxes are a gateway craft.

02:19.836 --> 02:21.703
Guess what, Tom?

02:21.737 --> 02:24.238
You've been caught in
some kind of lie and I,

02:24.273 --> 02:26.940
being the Queen of All Lies,
need to know what it is.

02:26.975 --> 02:29.241
Well...

02:29.276 --> 02:31.610
Nancy has been my girlfriend for a while.

02:31.644 --> 02:33.812
Oh, my gosh, you have a girlfriend! -

02:33.846 --> 02:35.046
Max, you have a girlfriend.

02:35.080 --> 02:37.114
Wait, wait. OK. OK. OK, I'm sorry.

02:37.148 --> 02:38.482
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

02:38.516 --> 02:42.018
What's wrong with her?
Booger eater? Bathroom snacker?

02:42.052 --> 02:44.854
Snort laugher? What is it?

02:44.888 --> 02:48.056
All that. That's what makes her great.
She's super gross.

02:48.090 --> 02:51.558
Aww. - Aww, you're gonna
be together forever.

02:51.593 --> 02:53.760
Do me a favor, though.
Don't tell Mom and Dad.

02:53.794 --> 02:55.227
I'm afraid they're gonna do something

02:55.262 --> 02:57.029
really embarrassing and scare her away.

02:57.063 --> 03:00.631
Max, I appreciate you wanting
to lie about having our parents,

03:00.665 --> 03:02.899
but changing your first name
isn't going to fool anyone.

03:02.934 --> 03:05.902
Oh, no, I know. But I changed
my last name, too, to Sawyer.

03:05.936 --> 03:08.036
-

03:08.071 --> 03:10.038
- This kid.
- Tom Sawyer?

03:10.072 --> 03:12.439
- Yeah.
- That's such an obvious lie.

03:12.474 --> 03:15.508
It's the name from the Rush song.

03:18.045 --> 03:20.446
And the classic book.

03:20.480 --> 03:24.482
Wow, that song was good,
I didn't know they made a book out of it.

